Package: tulpa
Title: Template Unified Latent Process Architecture for Bayesian Hierarchical Models
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R:
    person("Gilles", "Colling", , "gilles.colling@univie.ac.at", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3070-6066"))
Description: A general-purpose engine for fitting Bayesian hierarchical models with
    spatial fields, temporal effects, spatially varying coefficients, and multiple
    inference backends. Provides scalable spatial approximations (HSGP, NNGP, ICAR,
    BYM2), temporal structure (RW1/RW2, AR1, GP), and a tier-based inference system
    with epistemic guarantees (HMC/NUTS, Laplace approximation, variational inference).
    Model-specific packages plug observation likelihoods into the engine via a
    templated callback interface.
